                <head>132. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On November 21, 1961, the intelligence community issued Special National
                    Intelligence Estimate 11-14-61, “The Soviet Strategic Military Posture,
                    1961-1967.” The estimate sought to “reassess the broad outlines of the<gloss
                        target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>ʼs military doctrine and posture in the light
                    of recent information on Soviet strategic thinking, present military
                    capabilities, and R&amp;D in major weapons systems, and to estimate future
                    trends in Soviet military strategy and force structure.” For text, see <ref
                        target="frus1961-63v08#pg_198">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1961–1963, volume VIII, pages
                        198</ref>–<ref target="frus1961-63v08#pg_209">209</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
